<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870304-0003 </DOCNO><HL> Sara Lee to AcquireStake in French Firm</HL><DD> 03/04/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> SLETENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> CHICAGO  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Sara Lee Corp. said it agreed to invest about $84 million in DIM S.A., a Paris-based hosiery maker.    The investment, which is subject to approval by the French government, will give Sara Lee about a 34% interest in DIM, a unit of BIC S.A. of Paris.    Under the agreement, Sara Lee will buy 360,537 newly issued DIM shares valued at about $51 million and lend DIM about $33 million. The loan is convertible at a later date into an additional 229,463 DIM shares.    DIM, which makes and markets hosiery and intimate apparel products throughout Europe, had annual sales of about $260 million in 1985. Sara Lee, a food and consumer products concern, makes and markets hosiery through its Hanes Hosiery and L'eggs Products divisions. </TEXT></DOC>